Pd.series(data) why it will be

pd.Series(data) is used to create a Series in pandas.

A Series is a one-dimensional array-like structure that stores:

data values

index values

It is similar to a single column in a table.

Syntax
pd.Series(data)
Example
import pandas as pd

a = [10, 20, 30]

s = pd.Series(a)

print(s)
Output
0    10
1    20
2    30
dtype: int64
Explanation
Part	Meaning
0,1,2	Index
10,20,30	Data values
dtype	Data type
Why do we use pd.Series()?
We use it:

to store one-dimensional data

to label data using indexes

for statistical operations

for easy data manipulation

Difference Between Series and DataFrame
Series	DataFrame
One-dimensional	Two-dimensional
Single column	Multiple columns
Example:

Series
Age
20
21
22
DataFrame
Name	Age
Ram	20
Shyam	21
Custom Index Example
import pandas as pd

s = pd.Series([90, 85, 88], index=["A", "B", "C"])

print(s)
Output
A    90
B    85
C    88
dtype: int64
Here:

A, B, C are custom indexes.

